{
  "text": "Bojańczyk and Walukiewicz also characterized interesting logically defined classes of tree languages [CITATION_1] . Again, their results are not couched in terms of preclones, but they can conveniently be expressed in this way.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1720912"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "1720912": {
      "title": "Characterizing EF and EX tree logics",
      "abstract": "We characterize the expressive power of EX, EF and EX+EF logics. These are the fragments of CTL built using the respective operators. We give a forbidden pattern characterization of the tree languages definable in these logics. The characterizations give optimal algorithms for deciding if a given tree language is expressible in one of the three logics."
    }
  }
}